A unique maritime adventure
At Heerema Marine Contractors, we do something new every day. We operate the world’s largest crane vessel and with them we transport, install, and remove offshore structures for the offshore energy markets. Our projects range from installing wind turbines, removing retired offshore oil and gas platforms, and installing platforms up to 50,000 metric tons. By joining us, you will play an important part in our unique maritime adventure.
In this role you will be able to contribute to the digital journey of HMC from day one. We are setting the scene for our digital strategy, now it is time to turn data into insights that matters for us and learn from digital technologies. The reward in your role is you being the ultimate digital translator. You demonstrate your technical skills in breaking down complex problems into smaller issues and solve the puzzles by data analysis, applying algorithms and models, and visualizing your results in an (interactive) way for end-users. For some digital ideas we will explore or work together with external parties or use on-the-shelve software applications.
Focus on your daily activities will be brought by adopting a “light” sprint-methodology aiming for results in a relentless pace, balancing focus by dedicated time spend on deep work, and flexibility through dedicated time to connect others.
Your role in the story
 You will work in sprints together with people from different departments and different skills and competences and determine together what is a feasible goal in a short period of time (time is fixed, result is flexible);
You will apply your technical data science skills to develop proof of concepts in these sprints for digital use cases that create added value for our company.
You might be asked to provide data analysis support on an urgent offshore issue to contribute to our operational efficiency.
You will contribute to creating an internal community for everyone interested in digital topics, programming and computing, and connect people or collaborate on digital developments;
You are contributing to further shape our digital environment and frameworks to shape the future of digitalization.
Who will you work with?
As direct report to our Manager Digitalization; Marjolein Koudijs ;you will work together with a small but growing team of data engineers, data scientists and BI analysts and collaborate with our colleagues from all departments, fleet and HES to create data-driven results.
Is this the job for you?
This role requires an enthusiastic and curious person who is looking for data to apply their digital skills. You are interested in understanding other departments and are able to translate a business problem or digital idea into a data puzzle to be solved by working towards a proof of concept matching the specified requirements. Problem-solving, analytical and result-driven are your strong competences.
You enjoy working independently on a technical problem but are also interested in working together within a data science team, third parties and with colleagues that own the problem or idea. You like giving presentations or demos and explaining your work to others.
You do not need to be a unicorn but understand your own learning objectives to improve your competences and experiences.
Furthermore, you have:
Minimum HBO/WO degree in Engineering, Computer science, Mathematics or related with a clear affinity for data science or AI in selected courses or graduation thesis;
Experience in computing/programming/mathematical/statistical skills applied on large datasets and advanced timeseries analysis is essential;
Strong programming skills preferably Python, R or Java including AI/ML frameworks (such as PyTorch, TensorFlow) and interactive visualization libraries (such as Ipywidgets, Plotly Dash);
Experience with working agile/SCRUM or comparable methodologies;
Familiar with PowerBI or comparable;
Independent analytical thinker;
Good communication skills in English, both spoken and written;
 The job level is determined based on years of experience combined with the level of technical data science skills.
Making the impossible possible offshore, this is what drives us at Heerema! To execute our offshore projects we must innovate, engineer and develop to find solutions for our clients’ challenges. We are passionate about sustainability and are guided by our Sustainability Roadmap to reduce our impact on the planet. Working with Heerema means working in an international, informal, and friendly environment where you will meet likeminded and passionate colleagues.
Here's why people love working with us
Working on challenging projects;
Extensive onboarding process and opportunities to develop;
A development program to allow your talents to flourish;
Fun Friday-afternoon get together with colleagues;
Excellent perks and benefits, including travel allowance and contributions to your pension and insurance;
Free exercise facilities;
A social safety net with committed colleagues around you;
Plenty of digital and real-world activities to get to know colleagues outside your team;
30 days off to fully recharge;
A modern and easily accessible office in Leiden.
Is this your dream job? Apply now!
We are looking forward to hearing from you. We are interested in your CV, but we mainly want to find out more about your ambitions, your personality, and what is your motivation to succeed. So be sure to include a brief cover letter explaining why you are the perfect fit for this position.
So hit the button, apply and make the impossible possible with Heerema. We’d love to meet you!
The application process
The application process will consist of an online assessment, two interviews and contract negotiations. At the end of the process, we will cordially welcome you aboard.

